>You look at your chosen mate pensively, almost nervously, from across the cramped room you now share.

>It all started six months ago, when aliens made first contact with humanity is a spectacular manner.
>Massive, multi-kilometer long ships appeared in the sky, one over every continent. Then they began to broadcast a message. Considering the message was in English, they were clearly watching Earth for a while.
>The message said: “We are the Minui. We have come to barter.”
>Not “we come in peace” or “we’re going to kill you,” but to barter.
>The UN was thrown into a frenzy, having not considered this. What could these “Minui” aliens want that humans have? Why barter when they could just take it by force?
>The answer was humanity itself. Humans are what they wanted.
>Or rather, the fraction of humanity that the aliens found desirable.
>As it turns out, much life in the galaxy evolved along a similar path, with up-right walking mammals with two sexes making up the bulk of advanced civilizations. Many of those civilizations are matriarchal, and suffer from a female-favoring gender skew. The Minui are included in this number.
>The aliens want men. Able, intelligent, breeding-age men. Genetics is a fickle branch of science, and it’s easier to enable interbreeding to acquire desirable traits than it is to engineer said traits from scratch.
>Their offer was thus; in exchange for leaving earth and swearing loyalty to the Minui Federation, the human volunteers would get citizenship, fulfilling employment, community, and be matched to a breeding-age female Minui to build a family with.
>The outcry from Earth was instant once it became clear that most of humanity was going to be left out in the cold, but the visitors didn’t care. They were here for a brain drain, and the opinions of most were discarded.
